s before its scheduled time of entry into the UK.</p>\n\n<p>Once these steps are carried out, you can travel to (and return from) <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/countries/eu-countries/\" title=\"PETS EU country\">most <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> countries</a> and <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/countries/noneu-countries/\" title=\"PETS non-EU country\">some non-<abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> countries</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Unlisted countries</h2>\n\n<p>An ‘unlisted’ country is any country not included in the list of <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> or non-<abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> countries. You need to take <a href=\"/take-pet-abroad/unlisted-countries\" title=\"extra steps\">extra steps if you return from an unlisted country</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Book the return journey before you leave</h2>\n\n<p>You must book your return journey in advance with a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/routes/\" title=\"Defra list of PETS routes and transport companies\"><abbr title=\"Pet Travel Scheme\">PETS</abbr>-approved sea, air or rail route.</a></p>\n\n<p>Most major ferry companies, airlines and rail operators are approved.</p>\n\n<h2>When you return to the UK</h2>\n\n<p>Your pet&rsquo;s microchip will be scanned and its passport inspected.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you don’t have the correct paperwork or your pet hasn’t been prepared properly, it will be put into quarantine or sent back to the country it travelled from.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Travelling with multiple animals</h2>\n\n<p>There are <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/pet-owners\" title=\"extra rules\">extra rules</a> if you&rsquo;re travelling with more than 5 cats, dogs or ferrets.</p>\n\n<h2>Other types of animal</h2>\n\n<p>There are different rules covering the movement of <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/other-animals\" title=\"other types of pets\">other types of pets.</a></p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/take-pet-abroad/unlisted-countries","slug":"unlisted-countries","order":2,"title":"Unlisted countries","body":"<p>Cats, dogs and ferrets travelling to unlisted countries must also:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>have a blood sample taken by a vet at least 30 days after it was vaccinated (the date of vaccination counts as day 0 and not day 1)</li>\n  <li>have passed the blood test (the vet will give you a compliance certificate) </li>\n  <li>wait 3 calendar months from the date the blood sample was taken before re-entering the UK</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The 3-month waiting period doesn’t apply if your pet was vaccinated and blood tested in the EU and issued with an EU pet passport before travelling to an unlisted country.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Other rules for unlisted countries</h2>\n\n<p>The above rules are for bringing your pet back to the UK from an unlisted country. Some unlisted countries may have other rules you need to follow before taking them there.</p>\n\n<p>Contact the Specialist Service Centre for Exports for more information.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Specialist Service Centre for Exports</strong>  <br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#080;&#101;&#116;&#101;&#120;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#067;&#097;&#114;&#108;&#105;&#115;&#108;&#101;&#064;&#097;&#104;&#118;&#108;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#080;&#101;&#116;&#101;&#120;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#115;&#046;&#067;&#097;&#114;&#108;&#105;&#115;&#108;&#101;&#064;&#097;&#104;&#118;&#108;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n01228 403600<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8:30am to 5pm</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/take-pet-abr